      <hedline>
        <hl1>EXPANSION BY CHINADOTCOM</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Craig S. Smith</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Smith, Craig S</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Peter Yip, chief executive of Hong Kong-based Internet company Chinadotcom, says it plans to invest $10 million in Chinese e-commerce joint venture with government and could spend up to $100 million on Chinese investments by end of next year; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Peter Yip, the chief executive of the Hong Kong-based Internet company Chinadotcom, said it planned to invest $10 million in a Chinese e-commerce joint venture with the government and could spend up to $100 million on Chinese investments by the end of next year. Mr. Yip spoke about the company's expansion plans in an interview with Reuters.</p>
        <p>Craig S. Smith (NYT)</p>
      </block>
